  <fr:p>First, we recall that the embedding-projection pair <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\mathsf {L}{\iota ^+};\alpha _A\right )\mathclose {}}\dashv \mathsf {purify}_A]]></fr:tex> <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-0020.xml"
addr="jms-0020"
title="Pointed dcpos with open positivity predicates are almost free">exists</fr:link> because <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> has an <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-0022.xml"
addr="jms-0022"
title="Open positivity predicate">open positivity predicate</fr:link> by <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-0027.xml"
addr="jms-0027"
title="Positively generated dcpos have open positivity predicates">virtue of</fr:link> its <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-0023.xml"
addr="jms-0023"
title="Positively generated dcpos">positive generation</fr:link>. Therefore, the statement of this lemma is well-formed.</fr:p>

  <fr:p>Because <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\mathsf {L}{\iota ^+};\alpha _A\right )\mathclose {}}\dashv \mathsf {purify}_A]]></fr:tex> is an embedding-projection pair, it remains only to check that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {purify}_A;\mathsf {L}{\iota ^+};\alpha _A]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:em>inflation</fr:em>, i.e. for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a:A]]></fr:tex> we must have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a \sqsubseteq  \alpha _A{\mathopen {}\left (\mathsf {L}{\iota ^+}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathsf {purify}_Aa\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. As the latter is equal to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\bigsqcup _{p:\mathsf {pos}\,a}a]]></fr:tex>, the inflation condition follows from our assumption that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-0023.xml"
addr="jms-0023"
title="Positively generated dcpos">positively generated</fr:link>.</fr:p>
