type="local"
href="jms-0023.xml"
addr="jms-0023"
title="Positively generated dcpos">positively generated</fr:link> <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-001S.xml"
addr="jms-001S"
title="Pointed dcpo">pointed</fr:link> dcpo; then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is canonically <fr:em>free</fr:em> on its <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-001P.xml"
addr="jms-001P"
title="The subdcpo spanned by positive elements">subdcpo of positive elements</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A^+]]></fr:tex>. More specifically, the embedding-projection pair <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\mathsf {L}{\iota ^+};\alpha _A\right )\mathclose {}}\dashv {A}\xrightarrow {{\mathsf {purify}_A}}{\mathsf {L}{A^+}}]]></fr:tex> <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-0020.xml"
addr="jms-0020"
title="Pointed dcpos with open positivity predicates are almost free">given by</fr:link> the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-0021.xml"
addr="jms-0021"
title="The “purification” map">purification map</fr:link> is an isomorphism of dcpos.</fr:p>
 
   
